			<h3 ><a href="#p270536">Re: Advice on E- Walker idea ?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=270536&amp;sid=997f162e51170ec827997083337808a2#p270536"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=84&amp;sid=997f162e51170ec827997083337808a2" style="color: #AA0000;" class="username-coloured">fechter</a></strong> &raquo; Thu May 20, 2010 10:33 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">I think it would be pretty hard to modify the knee walker without making it look klugy.<br /><br />Something like a small scooter with a seat might be close to what you need.   You can still push along with your feet if needed.  Most of these go pretty fast compared to walking, but you can always control the speed with the throttle.  Lower gearing would be helpful too.<br /><br />This one is no longer made, but there are similar ones out there, and most of them are fairly inexpensive.<br /><div class="inline-attachment">
		<dl class="file">
			<dt class="attach-image"><img src="./download/file.php?id=39319&amp;sid=997f162e51170ec827997083337808a2" alt="Vego IQ500.jpg" onclick="viewableArea(this);" /></dt>
			
