			<div class="content">Helena, welcome to the forum.  I know you asked about altering the knee kicker, but it looks like it would be difficult to alter without a full rebuild.  I.e., those wheels would still be a problem, just like they are without a motor, etc.<br /><br />I would think that a recumbent trike, delta or tadpole would be a better place to start.  With a clipless pedal and shoe you could pedal with one foot.  Then you could add a small hub motor with very little modification and you would have a safe ride for your local trails, etc.<br /><br />Good luck with whatever you decide to do.</div>

